  23 Sep 2008; Raúl Porcel <armin76@gentoo.org> xmltex-1.9-r2.ebuild:
  Add ~ia64 wrt #237202

  21 Sep 2008; Brent Baude <ranger@gentoo.org> xmltex-1.9-r2.ebuild:
  Marking xmltex-1.9-r2 ~ppc64 for bug 237202

  14 Sep 2008; Alexis Ballier <aballier@gentoo.org> xmltex-1.9-r1.ebuild:
  use latex-base in the old ebuild too...

  14 Sep 2008; Alexis Ballier <aballier@gentoo.org> xmltex-1.9-r2.ebuild:
  We need to depend on latex-base instead of tex base as we use latex to
  build the formats; by Christian Faulhammer <opfer@gentoo.org>, bug #237605

  04 Sep 2008; Alexis Ballier <aballier@gentoo.org> xmltex-1.9-r1.ebuild,
  xmltex-1.9-r2.ebuild:
  depend on virtual/tex-base; we dont really support tetex-2 these days

  02 Sep 2008; Alexis Ballier <aballier@gentoo.org> xmltex-1.9-r2.ebuild:
  keyword ~x86-fbsd

*xmltex-1.9-r2 (22 Aug 2008)

  22 Aug 2008; Alexis Ballier <aballier@gentoo.org>
  +files/format.xmltex.cnf, +xmltex-1.9-r2.ebuild:
  Cleanup of the ebuild: require at least tetex 3, install formats to
  var/lib/texmf, install files to texmf-site, install a fmtutil.d file,
  block tl-htmlxml-2007 since they collide now.

  22 Aug 2008; Alexis Ballier <aballier@gentoo.org> -xmltex-0.14-r1.ebuild,
  -xmltex-1.9.ebuild:
  remove old

  31 May 2008; <solar@gentoo.org> xmltex-1.9-r1.ebuild:
  - stable on amd64

  12 Mar 2007; Alexandre Buisse <nattfodd@gentoo.org> metadata.xml:
  Replaced text-markup by tex as maintaining herd (text-markup split).

  05 Feb 2007; Diego Pettenò <flameeyes@gentoo.org> ChangeLog:
  Regenerate digest in Manifest2 format.

  10 Sep 2005; Aron Griffis <agriffis@gentoo.org> xmltex-1.9-r1.ebuild:
  Mark 1.9-r1 stable on alpha

  10 Feb 2005; Mamoru KOMACHI <usata@gentoo.org> xmltex-1.9-r1.ebuild:
  Stable on x86 and ppc.

  07 Feb 2005; Aron Griffis <agriffis@gentoo.org> xmltex-1.9-r1.ebuild:
  add ~alpha

  28 Dec 2004; Dylan Carlson <absinthe@gentoo.org> xmltex-1.9-r1.ebuild:
  Keywords ~amd64.

